<SLUG> BC-BKC-UH </SLUG>
 COACH-HNS  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
UH narrows coaching search
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By JERRY WIZIG &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 2000, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL; 
The University of Houston men's basketball coaching search might
have reached its final three candidates.
</P>
<P>
   A source familiar with the process indicated Saturday that
Appalachian State's Buzz Peterson, Kent's Gary Waters and Ball
State's Ray McCallum appear to be in the final cutdown to hire a
successor for Clyde Drexler, who resigned March 30.
</P>
<P>
   None of the trio, all head coaches at Division I programs, was
available for comment Saturday. UH athletic director Chet Gladchuk,
who is conducting the search, declined to be anywhere near as
specific.
</P>
<P>
   Gladchuk on Saturday referred to his forecast of last week that
the new coach would be named by late this week. Gladchuk, who has
declined to name coaches already interviewed or viewed as serious
candidates, said he was ``not sure'' if the hire would be completed
any sooner.
</P>
<P>
   Also uncertain is the standing in the current process of UH
assistants Reid Gettys and George Walker, both of whom have applied
for the position and have met twice with Gladchuk.
</P>
<P>
   Peterson, a former player at North Carolina, has led Appalachian
State to at least 21 wins in each of the last three seasons in his
four years with the Southern Conference school. He previously was
associate head coach at Vanderbilt and an assistant at North
Carolina State.
</P>
<P>
   Waters has been head coach at Kent, a Mid-American Conference
school, for four years after seven seasons as an assistant at
Eastern Michigan and reportedly toured the UH campus with president
Arthur Smith and other UH officials.
</P>
<P>
   McCallum's seven seasons at Ball State, also an MAC program,
have been marked by NCAA Tournament appearances in 1994 and '95 and
this past season. His team played in the National Invitation
Tournament in 1997 and '98.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
