<P>
   FINANCE-PROTESTS _ WASHINGTON _ Thousands of anti-globalization
protestors roamed through the nation's capital Sunday but failed to
achieve their goal of preventing international finance ministers
from meeting. One group of demonstrators was hit with pepper spray,
but the protestors were generally peaceful. There were occasional
arrests, but nothing on the scale of the more than 600 who were
arrested Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
   (Dart/Schultz, Cox News Service)
