<P>
   HEAT-DEATHS _ DAYTON _ Findings from health authorities have
doubled the number of deaths linked to psychiatric medications
taken by the mentally ill during last summer's fierce Midwestern
heat wave. New figures from the U.S. Centers for Disease Control in
Atlanta and the Cook County Medical Examiner's Office in Chicago
show that at least 23 of the estimated 300 dead were mentally ill
people who took medicines that made them especially vulnerable to
death from intense summer heat. The total number could be higher
still since not all coroners where heat deaths occurred performed
toxicology tests. (Bennish, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
