around when the chicken was served. In those days, a family of four
shared one (1) fried chicken. A family of 14 also shared one (1)
fried chicken. Those were the rules of the game. These days, cooks
buy chicken parts. Everybody gets a fat thigh or half a chicken
breast as their portion of the feasts.
