 &UR; PERKS _ &LR;  Last week, Oracle Corp. employee Amy Odum did something
that could have gotten her fired at some companies. Using her
office computer, she went online and bought health insurance for
Buster, her miniature schnauzer. Odum didn't get in trouble
shopping on company time because Oracle allows her to buy
discounted goods and services at a new employees-only shop on the
company's internal computer network. It's all part of an employee
Web portal designed and run by San Francisco startup
Perksatwork.com.  &UR; BY CARRIE KIRBY &LR;
