   STUDENT-DRUG-TESTS (Lockney, Texas) _ For three years, people in
this tiny farming town fretted that stopping the local drug problem
was like trying to lasso the winds that blow day and night off the
flat Texas plains. Eventually, the school board enacted what is
considered the toughest school drug testing policy in the nation.
It requires that all of the 388 junior and senior high school
students take a mandatory drug test. Now, with more and more school
districts across the country instituting drug tests, Lockney, with
only 2,200 residents, has become an unlikely constitutional
battleground. By Jim Yardley.
