A8613 &Cx1f; tad-z
u r BC-NASCAR-SIDE0417-COX     04-16 0434
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NASCAR-SIDE0417-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Wreck finally arrives, takes 16
 &HT;    By Rick Minter
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   TALLADEGA, Ala. _ The Big Wreck is one of the trademarks of a
NASCAR race at Talladega Superspeedway. This time it came on lap
138 _ 50 laps from the finish of Sunday's DieHard 500.
</P>
<P>
   Sixteen drivers were involved, including Bobby Labonte who
entered the race with the Winston Cup points lead but left in
second place, 24 points behind Mark Martin, who finished sixth.
</P>
<P>
   Labonte drove his battered Pontiac to a 21st-place finish _ his
worst of the 2000 season.
</P>
<P>
   ``It could have been a lot worse,'' he said. ``We just lost one
lap and were able to get back some positions that we maybe didn't
deserve after being involved in a big wreck like that.''
</P>
<P>
   Labonte said multi-car crashes are not unexpected.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not going to happen all the time, but the chances of it
happening are pretty big. And usually when it happens, it's pretty
big.''
</P>
<P>
   For more than half of Sunday's race, drivers had run three- and
four-cars wide without incident.
</P>
<P>
   But just after a restart, Scott Pruett appeared to cut in front
of Robby Gordon heading into turn one. When the smoke cleared, 16
wrecked cars were strewn across the track.
</P>
<P>
   Other drivers involved were Dick Trickle, Steve Park, Tony
Stewart, Dale Earnhardt Jr., Michael Waltrip, Mike Bliss, Stacy
Compton, Robert Pressley, Joe Nemechek, Ted Musgrave, Dave Blaney,
Ricky Rudd and Ken Schrader.
</P>
<P>
   Both Pruett and Gordon were at least a lap behind the leaders,
but were running in the lead draft.
</P>
<P>
   Pruett said he got hit from behind.
</P>
<P>
   ``It lifted the car up, got it light and turned it, so I
corrected it,'' Pruett said. ``That was that. It was a bad day.
...We were just racing hard, and I feel bad about all that.''
</P>
<P>
   Gordon said Pruett made a miscalculation when he moved into the
left line of traffic.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think Scott thought he was clear or maybe he noticed I had a
run and he was trying to get in line before being left out,''
Gordon said.
</P>
<P>
   Several drivers were checked out at the track's care center.
Only Trickle, who suffered a swollen right foot, will require
further treatment.
</P>
<P>
   Waltrip, like most other drivers in the crash, also said he was
minding his own business up to that point.
</P>
<P>
   ``They just drove into me,'' he said. ``I was so proud of this
group of drivers for running three- and four-wide and trying to
take care of each other. Just one mistake and you get a wreck like
that. It's unfortunate.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
