<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SUNDAY, APRIL 16
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Sunday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(ss) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MARINE-PLANE-CRASH-NYT (moved Monday, April 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, April 10
about the history of the military's V-22 Osprey program
misidentified the aircraft the Marines had sought to replace with
the Osprey. It was the Sea Knight helicopter, not the Chinook.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEDICAL-INFO-NYT (moved Saturday, April 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, April 8
about companies that make health care information available to
their employees misidentified the headquarters of HealthAllies,
which negotiates discounts for services that are often not covered
by health plans. It is based in Glendale, Calif., not Scottsdale,
Ariz.
</P>
