the past couple of weeks, I've had a chance to find out for myself.
I've been testing three new PCs with processors that run at
gigahertz speeds _ 1,000 megahertz, or 1 billion clock cycles per
second. (By way of context, a gigahertz is 200 times the speed of
the original 1981 IBM PC, and twice the speed of the fastest PC
chip available just 14 months ago.)  &UR; WITH SIDEBAR. &LR; 
 &UR; REVIEW BY HENRY NORR &LR;
